# Error Handling & Logging

## Console Logging Patterns

### Emoji-Based Status Indicators

Use consistent emoji patterns for different types of operations:

- `🚀` - Starting operations
- `✅` - Successful completion
- `❌` - Errors and failures
- `⚠️` - Warnings and skipped items
- `📊` - Statistics and counts
- `📈` - Progress updates
- `📝` - File operations and logs
- `💾` - Memory usage
- `🦊` - Export operations
- `⏳` - Processing status

### Logging Format

```typescript
console.log("🚀 ~ Starting operation ⏳");
console.log(`📊 ~ Total items to process: ${totalCount}`);
console.log(`📈 ~ Progress: ${processed}/${total} items processed`);
console.log("✅ ~ Operation completed");
console.error("❌ ~ Operation failed:", error);
```

## Error Handling Patterns

### Try-Catch Structure

```typescript
try {
  console.log("🚀 ~ Starting operation ⏳");
  await performOperation();
  console.log("✅ ~ Operation completed");
} catch (error) {
  const errorMessage = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);
  console.error("❌ ~ Operation failed:", errorMessage);
  throw error;
}
```

### Error Message Extraction

Always extract meaningful error messages:

```typescript
const errorMessage = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);
```

### Graceful Error Handling

```typescript
try {
  const result = await operation();
  return result;
} catch (error) {
  console.error(`❌ Operation failed:`, error);
  // Log to file for later analysis
  await logErrorToFile(error, context);
  // Return fallback or rethrow based on context
  throw error;
}
```

## File-Based Error Logging

### Error Log Structure

Create timestamped error logs in `strapi/logs/`:

```typescript
const currentTime = new Date().toISOString();
const errorLogPath = `strapi/logs/error-operation-${currentTime}.csv`;

// Initialize log with headers
await writeDataToCSV(
  `id,title,operation,error`,
  errorLogPath,
);

// Log errors during processing
await writeDataToCSV(
  `"${itemId}","${itemTitle}","${operation}","${errorMessage.replace(/"/g, '""')}"`,
  errorLogPath,
);
```

### CSV Error Logging

Use CSV format for structured error logs:

```typescript
const errorRow = `"${id}","${title}","${operation}","${errorMessage.replace(/"/g, '""')}"`;
await writeDataToCSV(errorRow, errorLogPath);
```

### Error Log Headers

Standard headers for different error types:

- `template_id,title,slug,error` - Form upload errors
- `template_id,title,operation,error` - Update operation errors
- `template_release_id,template_name,pdf_url,review_import_status,error` - PDF download errors

## Memory Management

### Memory Usage Logging

Use [logMemoryUsage](mdc:strapi/utils/helpers.ts) helper:

```typescript
import { logMemoryUsage } from "./utils/helpers.ts";

logMemoryUsage("Before execution");
await performOperation();
logMemoryUsage("After execution");
```

### Memory Monitoring Pattern

```typescript
export function logMemoryUsage(label: string) {
  const usage = Deno.memoryUsage();
  console.log(`💾 Memory [${label}]:`);
  console.log(`   RSS: ${(usage.rss / 1024 / 1024).toFixed(2)} MB`);
  console.log(`   Heap Used: ${(usage.heapUsed / 1024 / 1024).toFixed(2)} MB`);
  console.log(`   Heap Total: ${(usage.heapTotal / 1024 / 1024).toFixed(2)} MB`);
}
```

## Progress Reporting

### Chunked Processing Progress

```typescript
for (let i = 0; i < data.length; i += chunkSize) {
  const chunk = data.slice(i, i + chunkSize);
  await processChunk(chunk);

  console.log(
    `📈 ~ Progress: ${Math.min(i + chunkSize, data.length)}/${data.length} items processed`,
  );
}
```

### Statistics Reporting

```typescript
console.log("✅ ~ Operation completed");
console.log(`📊 ~ Total processed: ${totalProcessed}`);
console.log(`❌ ~ Total failed: ${totalFailed}`);
console.log(`📝 ~ Error log: ${errorLogPath}`);
```

## Validation Error Handling

### Input Validation

```typescript
public validateInput(data: FormData): { errors: string[]; isValid: boolean } {
  const errors: string[] = [];
  
  if (!data.title) {
    errors.push("Title is required");
  }
  
  if (data.title && data.title.length > MAX_LENGTH) {
    errors.push(`Title too long: ${data.title.length}`);
  }
  
  return {
    errors,
    isValid: errors.length === 0
  };
}
```

### Validation Error Logging

```typescript
const { isValid, errors } = this.validateInput(data);
if (!isValid) {
  console.log(`⚠️ Skipping invalid item: ${data.title || data.id}`);
  await writeDataToCSV(
    `"${data.id}","${data.title || ""}","validation","${errors.join("; ").replace(/"/g, '""')}"`,
    errorLogPath,
  );
  return;
}
```

## API Error Handling

### HTTP Response Handling

```typescript
const response = await fetch(endpoint, options);
const result = await response.json();

if (!response.ok || result.error) {
  const errorMessage = result.error?.message ||
    `HTTP ${response.status}: ${response.statusText}`;
  console.error(`❌ API call failed:`, errorMessage);
  throw new Error(errorMessage);
}
```

### Network Error Handling

```typescript
try {
  const response = await fetch(url, options);
  return await response.json();
} catch (error) {
  const errorMessage = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);
  console.error(`❌ Network error:`, errorMessage);
  throw error;
}
```

## Retry Logic

### Download Retry Pattern

```typescript
public downloadPDF(url: string, outputPath: string, retries = 3): Promise<void> {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    fetch(url, options)
      .then(async (response) => {
        // Process response
        resolve();
      })
      .catch(async (err) => {
        if (retries > 0) {
          console.log(`Retrying download... (${retries} attempts remaining)`);
          try {
            await this.downloadPDF(url, outputPath, retries - 1);
            resolve();
          } catch (error) {
            reject(error);
          }
        } else {
          reject(err);
        }
      });
  });
}
```

## Error Recovery

### Fallback Operations

```typescript
try {
  await this.downloadPDF(url, path);
} catch (error) {
  console.log(`⚠️ Attempting fallback download`);
  try {
    await this.downloadPDFWithFetch(url, path);
    console.log(`✅ Fallback successful`);
  } catch (fallbackError) {
    throw new Error(`Both primary and fallback downloads failed`);
  }
}
```
